# One Stall, Everywhere

The player's stall is a single, canonical UI. It must **look and behave the same
way any time it is displayed** in the game (shop, battle prep, boss-reward
screen, and any future screen).

## Rules

- **Reuse the real `#board` element.** There is exactly one stall DOM node
  (`#board.stall-tray`, rendered by `renderStall` in `src/ui/components/cards.ts`).
  When another screen needs the stall, move/borrow that element and restore it on
  close — never build a second, parallel stall markup.
- **No bespoke restyling.** Do not wrap the stall in a container that changes its
  borders, radius, background, sizing, or grid. The stall carries all its own
  styling via `#board.stall-tray`. Panels/overlays may sit **above** the stall,
  not around it.
- **Identical interactions.** Drag, sell, merge, and reorder must work the same
  everywhere. This is automatic if you reuse `#board` and keep `isShopActive()`
  (in `src/app.ts`) returning true for the context, and call `refreshShop()` /
  the relevant refresh so synergy glows and fit-state stay in sync.

## Example: showing the stall under a panel

```ts
// ✅ GOOD — panel on top, the real stall mounted natively beneath it.
overlay.appendChild(panelCard);
overlay.appendChild(board); // the real #board, no special wrapper

// ❌ BAD — a styled host box that gives the stall a different look.
panelCard.innerHTML = `<div class="my-stall-host">...</div>`;
host.appendChild(board); // now boxed/restyled, inconsistent with shop
```
